  • Constructor Details

    • VideoBox

      public VideoBox​(Video video, StatisticsPaneView statisticsPaneView)
      This constructor creates a new VideoBox element, that takes care of playing the video, managing pause/play button, the slider to manage the timeline of the video and the interactions related to the video. It's meant to be used when the videobox is created by statisticsPage of the professor so it won't use the username of the student and the videoPlayerArea.
      Parameters:
      video - the video entity (from the db) that will be displayed

    • VideoBox

      public VideoBox​(VideoPlayerArea videoPlayerArea, Video video, java.lang.String username)
      This constructor creates a new VideoBox element, that takes care of playing the video, managing pause/play button, the slider to manage the timeline of the video and the interactions related to the video. This contructor is meant to be used by the videoBoxAreaView class when it creates the videoBox element.
      Parameters:
      videoPlayerArea - : the contoller of the videoBoxAreaView that created this video box.
      video - the video entity (from the db) that will be displayed
      username - the username of the student that is currently posting the interactions and questions.

      public void listen​(Event event)
      Description copied from interface: Listener
      The listen method is overwritten from all classes that implement this interface. Each class will handle the Event that they receive and will act accordingly
      Specified by:
      listen in interface Listener
      Parameters:
      event - generic event received from a dispatch method of some other classes. This event can be extended in other subclasses in order to implement the polimorphysm.
